- "shining star" refers to the top goal scorer;
- "leads the pack" indicates the player with the highest rank;
- "standing tall" emphasizes the top position.

- "shone bright" refers to a high average number of wins;
- "faced the least defeats" refers to a low average number of losses;
- "played to a draw" refers to the average number of draws.

sql:
SELECT 
    AVG(
        CAST(SUBSTR(full_time_score, 1, INSTR(full_time_score, '-') - 1) AS INTEGER) +
        CAST(SUBSTR(full_time_score, INSTR(full_time_score, '-') + 1) AS INTEGER)
    ) AS overall_average_goals
FROM matches;

